Getting Started
Prerequisites
This tool requires Python 3 and a few libraries. You can install them with pip.

Bash

# Update package list
sudo apt-get update

# Install python3 and pip
sudo apt-get install python3 python3-pip -y

# Install project dependencies
pip3 install Flask Faker
Installation
Clone the repository to your server:

Bash

git clone https://github.com/your-username/cortex-syslog-generator.git
cd cortex-syslog-generator
Create the Python file: Create a file named app.py in the project directory.

Bash

nano app.py
Add the code: Copy the entire code from this project's repository and paste it into the app.py file. Save and exit the file.

Usage
Run the application:

Bash

python3 app.py
The application will start, and you will see a message indicating it is running on all addresses on port 5000.

Access the web UI: Open a web browser and navigate to http://[SERVER_IP_ADDRESS]:5000. If you encounter a connection error, ensure your server's firewall is not blocking port 5000.

Configure and Generate:

Enter the IP address of your Cortex Broker.

Select a Log Format and one or more Log Sources.

Choose between Randomization and Story mode. For Story mode, you can also enable Add Noise to increase realism.

Click Start to begin sending logs.

